# Code Style

- Write components and hooks in TypeScript with explicit, readable types.
- Keep components focused; extract repeated UI or logic into reusable components.
- Use clear names for files, components, props, and CSS classes.
- Prefer simple, predictable JSX over deeply nested markup.
- Keep imports tidy and remove unused code before finishing.
- No inline styles

# UI Conventions

- Use Ant Design components first, then extend with CSS classes for custom design.
- Keep visual consistency with existing spacing, typography, and color patterns.
- For responsive behavior, follow existing breakpoints and avoid one-off hacks.

# Example

```tsx
// Good: clear props + focused component
type SectionTitleProps = { title: string; subtitle?: string }

function SectionTitle({ title, subtitle }: SectionTitleProps) {
  return (
    <header>
      <h2>{title}</h2>
      {subtitle ? <p>{subtitle}</p> : null}
    </header>
  )
}
```
